                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "K-400 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The stacked foils is 2.160 mm and 2.0 cm in thickness",
                "and diameter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced by the T(d,n)4He",
                "reaction with an effective deuteron beam energy and",
                "current is 135 keV and 260 uA. The T-Mo target",
                "thickness is 0.566 mg/cm2 and an active zone diameter",
                "of 1.2 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The crystal geometry is 70.1 x 72.3 mm in",
                "diameter and length. The relative efficiency is about",
                "68%, and energy resolution is 1.69 keV at 1332 keV",
                "gamma ray from Co-60. The efficiency of the detector",
                "was pre-calibrated using various standard gamma",
                "sources, which were Co-57, Co-60, Cd-109, Ba-133,",
                "Cs-137, Eu-152, Am-241 and Ra-226."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Au-Si surface barrier detector used in",
                "the 135-deg accompanying alpha-particle tube was 110",
                "cm from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The sample was irradiated and lasted around",
                "24 hours with a yield around 3 to 4E10 n/(4pi*s). The",
                "sample groups were placed at 0, 90 or 135 degree",
                "relative to the beam direction and centered about the",
                "T-Mo target at distances of around 4 cm. During",
                "irradiation, the neutron flux was monitored by",
                "accompanying alpha particles so that corrections",
                "could be made for small variations in the yield."
              ]
            }
          ],
